Defendant Cody L Naleck in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that he met with the defendant and an offer had been provided; in speaking with the defendant before court, he would like to accept that offer.    Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant agrees.    Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant waives their right to an attorney.    Court finds waiver made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.
Defendant enters a Guilty plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty.

Atty Hendee asks the court to follow the recommendation.
